The paper proposes a novel motion planning algorithm that employs stochastic optimization based on the cross-entropy method to tackle the local minima problem. The paper also introduces heteroscedasticity to generate powerful trajectory priors better suited for collision avoidance in motion planning problems. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Robotics (cs.RO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Systems and Control (cs.SY), and Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-categories.
